          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1679331146558-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the aubergine is cooking, wash, then chop the <strong>roots</strong> from your <strong>pak choi </strong>and separate the leaves, discarding the roots</p><p>Chop any <strong>larger leaves</strong> in half </p><p>Trim your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong>, then chop each<strong> </strong>spring onion into thirds</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Rinse your <strong>blanched edamame beans</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1679331149063-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1679331149063-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
